    <!-- ── FAQ ── -->
    <section class="faq" id="faq">
      <p class="section-tag">Common questions</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">Everything you need<br />to know.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div class="faq-inner">
        <div class="faq-list">
          <div class="faq-item open">
            <button class="faq-q">
              What exactly is bookkeeping, and why do I need it?
              <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a">
              <p>
                Bookkeeping is the process of recording and organizing every
                financial transaction in your business or personal finances —
                income, expenses, payments, and receipts. Without it, you're
                flying blind. Clean books make it possible to file your taxes
                accurately, spot cash flow issues early, and make confident
                financial decisions.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q">
              Do you work with individuals or just businesses?
              <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a">
              <p>
                Both. We work with freelancers, independent contractors, sole
                proprietors, LLCs, S-Corps, and small businesses. Whether you're
                a single person with self-employment income or a growing company
                with employees, we tailor our services to fit your situation.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q">
              My books are a mess. Can you still help?
              <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a">
              <p>
                Absolutely — that's one of the most common situations we deal
                with. We offer catch-up bookkeeping services to go back through
                your records, clean everything up, and get you fully current. We
                don't judge; we just fix it.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q">
              How does the process work? Where do I start?
              <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a">
              <p>
                Start with a free consultation. We'll talk about your situation,
                assess what you need, and put together a plan. From there, you
                share your financial documents and we get to work. The whole
                onboarding process is straightforward and we walk you through
                every step.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q">
              Do I need to provide anything to get started?
              <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a">
              <p>
                We'll need access to your bank statements, existing records (if
                any), and a few basic details about your income and expenses.
                We'll give you a clear checklist after your consultation so you
                know exactly what to gather — nothing more than what's
                necessary.
              </p>
